title: breach
description: In February, 2001, Robert Hanssen, a senior agent with 25 years in the FBI, is arrested for spying. Jump back two months: Eric O&#039;Neill, a computer specialist who wants to be made an agent is assigned to clerk for Hanssen and to write down everything Hanssen does. O&#039;Neill&#039;s told it&#039;s an investigation of Hanssen&#039;s sexual habits. Within weeks, the crusty Hanssen, a devout Catholic, has warmed to O&#039;Neill, who grows to respect Hanssen. O&#039;Neill&#039;s wife resents Hanssen&#039;s intrusiveness; the personal and professional stakes get higher. How they catch Hanssen and why he spies become the film&#039;s story. Can O&#039;Neill help catch red-handed "the worst spy in history" and hold onto his personal life?
